The paper deals with decision-making and information structures, which are topics commonly studied in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of counterfactuals also suggests a connection to causal inference and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the construction of structures, which could fall under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) or information theory (cs.IT).
